<HEADLINE> Daimler-Benz to Sell Stake in Cap Gemini </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Germany's biggest industrial group
Dailmler-Benz said today it was selling its 24.4 percent stake in
Europe's biggest data processing firm, known as Cap Gemini, S.A.
</P>
<P>
Daimler-Benz would sell the stake to the CGIP, currently the
principle shareholder of the Paris-based company, for 1.4 billion
marks (800 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The group assured the holders of convertible bonds previously
issued by Cap Gemini that the securities would be redeemed at 104
percent of their face value. 
