<HEADLINE> Demonstrating Security Guards Shot in Harare, 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The manager of a security company
in Harare today opened fire on his demonstrating employees,
wounding 15 of his security guards, Zimbabwe News Agency Ziana
reported.
</P>
<P>
Details of what exactly transpired outside the Fawcett
Security Company Fawcett Headquarters were sketchy with the
officer commanding Harare province senior assistant
commissioner Osborne Mawere saying he was still to receive a full
report from the investigating team.
</P>
<P>
However, witnesses said that Fawcett General Manager D.B.
Thomas opened fire on the security guards in full view of the
police riot squad who were monitoring the otherwise peaceful
demonstration.
</P>
<P>
Members of the riot squad were said to have taken cover as
Thomas, who was later picked up by the police, fired on the
demonstrators.
</P>
<P>
Thomas allegedly fired from the roof of a guard room as the
security guards who are demanding a 50 percent salary increase
sang revolutionary songs outside the company.
</P>
<P>
Officials at Harare Hospital's casualty department confirmed
that Fawcett Security Guards had been brought to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe has been hit by a spate of strikes beginning Monday
with workers from the construction, clothing, cement, lime and
national railways of Zimbabwe downing their tools demanding
better salaries. 
</P>
