southern Africa. We will do well to look first for these products
in Africa,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Zinsou arrived in Zimbabwe Wednesday and is expected to leave
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He is the special advisor to President Kerekou on
international issues and is also former president and foreign
minister of the west African nation.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''I have come with a friendly message to President
Mugabe so that we can have development ties in economic, cultural
and political fields.'' 
