<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Support Rates for Chirac, Jospin Rise Considerably </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- One month after the beginning of
right-left cohabitation between President Jacques Chirac and
Prime Minister Lionel Jospin, the support rates for both men have
risen considerably in June, according to Agence France-Presse
(AFP).
</P>
<P>
AFP quoted a poll conducted by the Louis Harris polling
institute as saying that the support rate of Jospin rose by 5
points to 48 percent within one month, while that of Chirac rose
by 10 points to 42 percent.
</P>
<P>
The IPSOS polling institute said that the support rate of
Jospin rose by eight points to 52 percent, while that of Chirac
rose by 11 points to 46 percent, according to AFP.
</P>
<P>
The Gallup polling group said that the support rate of Chirac
grew by three points to 47 percent in June as was compared with
March 1997, while the support rate of Jospin, which appeared for
the first time in the barometer of the polling group, stood at 59
percent by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
The drop in the number of people who failed to express their
opinions has greatly contributed to the rise of popular rate of
Chirac, said AFP. 
</P>
