<HEADLINE> AL Chief Supports Lebanon's Resistance against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Esmat Abdul-Meguid, secretary
general of the League of Arab States, stressed here this evening
his support for Lebanon's resistance against the Israeli
occupation in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after his meeting with Lebanese Foreign
Minister Farez Boueiz, he underlined the necessity for Lebanon to
continue the resistance until the Israeli occupation in the south
is eliminated, affirming the "legitimacy" of the resistance.
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Meguid called on the Lebanese people to uphold their
national unity in the cause of resistance, noting that the unity
will make it impossible for Israel to continue the occupation.
</P>
<P>
"We should not look at the south Lebanon problem as if it is
only of Lebanon, but it is a problem of all of us, and the
Lebanese are adhering to their firmness," the Arab League chief
said.
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Meguid arrived here from Cairo this afternoon to
attend the opening ceremony of the Eighth Pan-Arab Games which is
to be held in the Beirut Sports City Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Abdul-Meguid held a meeting with Boueiz
during which they exchanged views on latest developments in the
region.
</P>
<P>
"We exchanged views on a number of proposals and a number of
initiatives which have been put forward, especially those by
Europe," Boueiz told a press conference held at the end of the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese foreign minister noted that they have "identical
opinions of pessimism" on the present situation of the peace
process due to the intransigence of Israeli Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
Boueiz announced that he and Abdul-Meguid reached an agreement
on steps which should be taken in the future to politically
activate the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League secretary general, on the other hand,
expressed his aspiration for progress in the peace process,
saying that efforts should continuously be made in order to
overcome the difficulties in the process.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Arab countries are committed to their
"well-known" positions and they are continuously sticking to the
basis of the peace process. He urged the United States to exert
efforts to avoid a failure of the process.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Abdul-Meguid stressed the significance for Lebanon
to hold the Eighth Pan-Arab Games "which will proves to the world
that Lebanon has regained its vitality and has consolidated its
position in the region."
</P>
<P>
After his talks with Boueiz, Abdul-Meguid held a meeting with
Lebanese House Speaker Nabih Berri.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League secretary general is to have meetings with
Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri and President Elias Hrawi
Friday. 
</P>
