<HEADLINE> Ecosystem in Kenya's Mt. Aberdare to Be </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government is
scheduled to undertake a resource development project in order to
rehabilitate the ecosystem in the Aberdare Mountain range,
according to a Kenya Times report today.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the African Development Bank (ADB) had
earmarked 35 million U.S. Dollars for the project.
</P>
<P>
A senior agricultural economist of the bank, Shiji Ojukwu, was
quoted as saying on Wednesday in Murang'a, about 70 kilometers
east of Nairobi, that the project would be completed within six
years.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the project has three components including
electrical fencing of the mountain range to reduce conflicts
between human beings and wild animals.
</P>
<P>
The project will cover sixth districts in Central Province
which share the mountain and the communities bordering the
Aberdare will be provided with piped water, access roads and
credit facilities to improve their economic base.
</P>
<P>
Ojukwu noted that the project, when completed, would make the
Aberdare a major tourist site and protect the local farmers
from the destruction of their crops by wild animals. 
</P>
