<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of 38 million U.S. dollars
in financing to support a program in Argentina that will empower
vulnerable population groups to obtain better access to essential
social services.
</P>
<P>
The project will promote the formation of human and social
capital in the fight to reduce poverty, improving equity in social
services. It will also help improve the organizational and
oversight capabilities of local government bodies, civil society,
