<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Minister Stresses Fiscal Discipline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Finance Minister Rabindra
Nath Sharma stressed today that it is essential to emphasize
fiscal discipline for sound and sustainable development of the
national economy.
</P>
<P>
To prevent the anomalies and aberrations likely to crop up from
the growing economic anarchy in the country, fiscal discipline is
necessary, Sharma told a press conference here on the 1997-98
fiscal year budget he presented to the parliament Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the parliament, he said since the government itself could
not adhere to fiscal discipline, overdrafts taken unrestrictedly
in the past years have caused negative impact on the national
economy.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the necessary bill will soon be introduced to limit
the government's authority to issue overdraft not exceeding one
billion rupees (17 million U.S. dollars) from the central bank, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In order to reduce the budget deficit, special measures will be
initiated to increase revenue, control tax leakage and curtail
unproductive expenditure, Sharma told the press conference.
</P>
<P>
And income tax and value added tax will be gradually developed
as major components of revenue mobilization, he added.
</P>
<P>
The finance minister said the budget is based on authentic
statistics, calling for cooperation from all quarters in its
implementation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
