<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Reduce Population Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam aims to cut its population
growth rate to 1.5-1.6 percent by the year 2000 and stabilize its
population at 120-125 million by the middle of the next century.
</P>
<P>
Mai Ky, cabinet minister and chairman of the National Committee
for Population and Family Planning, made the announcement here
today at a meeting to mark the 10th World Population Day.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's population growth was down to 1.88 percent in 1996
from 2.40 percent in 1992, but the government is aware of the fact
that it was still higher than the world's average of 1.48 percent.
</P>
<P>
Ky said the Vietnamese government has to find simultaneous
solutions to such problems as the size, structure, distribution
and quality of its population. 
</P>
