<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Hails Contribution of HKSAR Preparatory Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, Chairman of the National
People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, said here today that
the members of the Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) have made great contributions to the
smooth transition of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"The Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong SAR has finished
its historic mission. Since its establishment in January 1996 the
members of the committee have devoted themselves to hard work to
set up the Hong Kong SAR," noted Qiao.
</P>
<P>
His speech was made at the 10th plenary session of the
Preparatory Committee. The meeting announced the end of the
committee's work, according to a decision made by the 26th session
of the Standing Committee of the NPC.
</P>
<P>
"Ten days ago China announced the founding of the Hong Kong
SAR. Its administrative, legislative and judicial departments are
now exercising their respective functions," Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the smooth transition of Hong Kong to the overall
implementation of the Basic Law that is based on the fundamental
principles of "one country, two systems" and "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong".
</P>
<P>
"The NPC and its standing committee has always paid great
attention to Hong Kong's smooth transition, and prosperity and
stability, and have made their due contributions to Hong Kong's
return," Qiao noted.
</P>
<P>
The NPC passed a series of laws and decisions and set up the
Preliminary Working Committee of the Preparatory Committee and the
Preparatory Committee since the Third Session of the Seventh NPC
adopted the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Standing Committee of the NPC also established the Basic
Law Committee of the Hong Kong SAR on July 1 this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that the NPC will continue to support the work of the
Hong Kong SAR and help promote the future development of Hong
Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
