<HEADLINE> Hakkinen Comes First in British F1 Practice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Mika Hakkinen of Finland posted the
fastest time at Friday's practice for Sunday's British Formula One
Grand Prix in Silverstone.
</P>
<P>
Hakkinen clocked an imprissive time of one minute and 22.935
seconds, indicating that his McLaren team was the one to reckon
with in Sunday's 60-lap race.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Jacques Villeneuve, finished 0.3 seconds away from
Hakkinen, was the second fastest, and his Williams teammate
Heinz-Harald Frentzen of Germany was third-fastest.
</P>
<P>
Former world champion Michael Schumacher of Germany came
seventh for Ferrari and reigning world champion Damon Hill of
Britain got stuck in 20th place in his Arrows. 
</P>
