<HEADLINE> HK Shares Hit Record Closing High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices today
closed up 386.06 points, or 2.6 percent, to hit a record high of
15,225.29 points.
</P>
<P>
The previous record high of 15,195.79 points was set on June
27, the last trading day before the handover.
</P>
<P>
Today's gains were made across the board, with properties up
688.74 points, utilities 451.13 points, finance 429.26 points and
commerce and industry 214.14 points.
</P>
<P>
Local securities professionals said the market was spurred by
optimism on upcoming half-year results from several blue-chip
companies.
</P>
<P>
There were also strong buying on China-affiliated stocks, or
red chips, pushing the newly introduced index for the shares
134.43 points, or 4.2 percent, higher to close at 3,319.45 points.
</P>
<P>
The value of turnover amounted to 18.546 billion HK dollars
(2.396 billion U.S. dollars), up from the previous day's 14.751
billion HK dollars (1.891 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Following gains on Wall Street overnight, Hong Kong shares
opened higher with the key barometer, Hang Seng Index, rising
240.75 points by the end of the morning session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
