<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Landslides Kill 23 in South Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- At least 23 people including eight
children were killed and ten others injured in separate landslides
in south of Bangladesh due to torrential rains in the last three
days, local news agency BSS said today.
</P>
<P>
According to Bangladesh Sangbad Sangstha (BSS) reporting from
Chittagong city, 13 people from three families, mostly children
and women, were killed when several chunks of earth from a nearby
hill fell on their houses on the bank of Rangamati lake in the
early hours today.
</P>
<P>
The victims were asleep during the landslide occurred due to
incessant rainfall. Of the inhabitants, only three persons
survived and they were admitted to near hospital with critical
injuries.
</P>
<P>
In Chittagong, the largest port city in south Bangladesh, four
persons, including two minor girls were killed and six others
injured in two separate landslides at Station Road and Amin Jute
Mills last night.
</P>
<P>
In the southern Cox's Bazar district, one person was killed on
Thursday in a landslide in Moheskhali county while two others were
washed away by the flood water at Sadar County on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
According to another report from Bandarban district, three
persons including one 85-year-old woman were killed as they were
washed away by the flash flood water on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the last three days, the flash flood, coupled with
torrential rainfall, has marooned tens of thousands of people in
low-lying areas under 10 districts around Bangladesh.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
