<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Asks Mayors to Care for "Vegetable Baskets" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The system of mayors'
responsibility for "vegetable baskets" must be continued
unswervingly, Vice-Premier Li Lanqing told a national conference
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The State Council worked out the mayors' responsibility system
for the "vegetable baskets" in 1994, in a bid to ensure the urban
dwellers' basic living standards and social stability.
</P>
<P>
The mainstay role of the state-run enterprises in the markets
must be further improved, and a market system that suits the
socialist market system must be perfected to satisfy the people's
demands for vegetables and meat, Li said.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the goals, Li said, the production scales and the
technological level must be improved, the related reforms
deepened, agricultural by-product wholesale markets perfected, the
management and distribution of vegetables and by-products
developed, and the macro-control system strengthened and perfected.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that all localities must earnestly carry out the
stipulations in the State Council's latest circular about the
"vegetable basket" programme and continue the mayors'
responsibility system steadfastly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
