<HEADLINE> Preparatory Committee's Efforts for HKSAR Establishment Praised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Two of Hong Kong's Chinese
language newspapers published commentaries today, hailing the
great contributions the Preparatory Committee has made to the
establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
The Preparatory Committee is holding its tenth and last plenary
meeting in Beijing today to put an end to its operation after
successfully fulfilling the historic mission of making
preparations for the establishment of the HKSAR, Ta Kung Pao said.
</P>
<P>
Since its formation in January 1996, the committee has carried
out intense but orderly work -- forming the Selection Committee
for the First HKSAR Government, electing the first Chief Executive
and the Provisional Legislative Council, formulating the concrete
method for the formation of the first Legislative Council and
putting forward proposals for handling the then existing Hong Kong
laws.
</P>
<P>
The committee also made suggestions and advice on major
economic issues related to the handover of Hong Kong and its
smooth transition, as well as on arrangements for various
activities to celebrate Hong Kong's return to the motherland, the
Ta Kung Pao commentary said.
</P>
<P>
The commentary noted: "It is no exaggeration to say that the
committee has made great contributions to China's resumption of
the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, laid solid foundation
for the realization of "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong
people running Hong Kong" and a high degree of autonomy in Hong
Kong, and added a brilliant chapter to the history of the Chinese
nation."
</P>
<P>
Broad and active participation of Hong Kong people in the
preparatory work for establishing the HKSAR has played a decisive
role in the smooth operation of the Preparatory Committee, it also
noted.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Commercial Daily said in its commentary that Hong
Kong's return was hailed as "perfect" and so can be said of the
related work done by the Preparatory Committee.
</P>
<P>
Authorized by China's National People's Congress to prepare for
the establishment of the HKSAR, the committee has fully embodied
the principle of "facing Hong Kong people and relying on them" in
everything it has done, including its own formation. It also
sincerely implemented the principles of "one country, two
systems," "Hong Kong people running Hong Kong" and a high degree
of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said no body can have a deeper appreciation than
the Hong Kong people of the committee's contributions -- Hong
Kong underwent a smooth transition, the HKSAR Government was
inaugurated as scheduled, and the HKSAR got off to a good start
blessed with a stable society, a buoyant market and favorable
public opinions.
</P>
<P>
The committee has made historic contributions to Hong Kong's
long-term prosperity and stability and to the great cause of
reunification of the motherland, it concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
