<TEXT>
<P>
BABGKOK, July 11 (Xinhua) -- At least 70 people were killed as
a big fire blazed a five-star hotel in Thailand's famous seaside
tourism city of Pattaya today, local media reported.
</P>
<P>
The victims including foreign tourists were killed when the
disaster took place at the Royal Jomtien Resort Hotel, about 200
kilometers southeast of Bangkok, earlier this morning.
</P>
<P>
