<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in Police Firing in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed
and 34 others injured in police firing and incidents of stone
pelting and arson in the south Indian city of Bombay (Mumbai)
early today, Press Trust of India (PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
The trouble was sparked off following the desecration of a
statue of B.R. Ambedkar, author of the Indian constitution, by
unidentified miscreants in northeast Bombay, according to police.
</P>
<P>
The statue of Ambedkar, who was from the minority community,
was found garlanded with slippers this morning.
</P>
<P>
Traffic on a busy highway in the city came to a grinding halt
as mobs stoned passing vehicles and a police post.
</P>
<P>
Reports said police opened fire on a group of people who tried
to torch a luxury bus and set afire an oil tanker.
</P>
<P>
Many people were injured in the firing and rushed to a local
hospital where 10 of them succumbed to injuries.
</P>
<P>
Trouble also broke out in other areas of the metropolitan, PTI
said.
</P>
<P>
Senior local police officials said the situation was "tense but
under control." 
</P>
</TEXT>
