<HEADLINE> 6 Killed by Tamil Rebels in East Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Six persons were killed by Tamil
rebels today when they attacked police personnel in the Eastern
province of Sri Lanka, according to military sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said Tamil rebels attacked a group of police
personnel proceeding from Toppur police station to Pahala Toppur
police post in Trincomalee district this morning.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fired indiscriminately with small arms which
resulted in the killing of one pregnant lady, a 7-year old child
and four other civilians who had come to the Pahala Toppur
dispensary for treatment. 16 civilians who were bathing at a
bathing spot were injured.
</P>
<P>
Government troops were rushed to the area and the rebels fled,
the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a guerrilla war for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country since
1983. 
</P>
