<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Silence from the Reserve Bank of
Australia on official interest rates drove the Australian dollar
to tight trading today with the local currency lifting only
slightly to the close.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 74.44 US cents, up from 74.33 at
Thursday's close.
</P>
<P>
One dealer said, today's trading movement was "a reflection of
a very short market."
</P>
<P>
Expectation of a cut to official interest rates was heightened
after Thursday's release of labor force data for June, which
pointed to weaker-than-expected jobs growth.
</P>
<P>
Another dealer said, gold's price increase today had added its
support to the local unit.
</P>
<P>
Gold bullion closed trade in Sydney at 320.75 US dollars an
ounce from 319.60 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The fall in housing finance by volume of 8.4 percent in May was
larger than economists had expected.
</P>
<P>
However, trend figures showing a slight increase in total
dwellings financed in May were in line with forecasts.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished at 84.71 from 83.74 against
Japanese yen and was at 1.3058 from 1.3113 against German marks.
</P>
</TEXT>
