<HEADLINE> Pierce out of Federation Cup Semi-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 11 (Xinhua) -- France's Mary Pierce will withdraw
from the Federation Cup tennis semi-final with Belgium in Nice
This weekend because of her shoulder injury.
</P>
<P>
Alexandra Fusai replaces Pierce and opens the match against
Sabine Appelmans on Saturday. Sandrine Testud, who beat Monica
Seles of the United States at Wimbledon Open, plays the second
rubber against Dominique Van Roost.
</P>
<P>
The reverse singles and doubles are played on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
