<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire on Maltese-Flag Freighter Put Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Firemen and coastguards today
extinguished the fire on a Maltese-flag freighter off Piraeus,
about 15 kilometers southwest of the Greek capital.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out Tuesday in the engine room of the
40,000-tonnage freighter "Anafi" which docked for repair off the
port.
</P>
<P>
Searches are still on for the vessel's first engineer, George
Markoulis, who has been missing since the fire broke out. The
other 30 persons aboard the ship have been rescued.
</P>
<P>
The ship, loaded with coal, was en route from China to
France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
