<HEADLINE> Clinton Starts Visit to Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 11 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
arrived here today for a one-day visit to mend ties with Romania
after the United States excluded Romania from the first group of
eastern European nations to join the NATO.
</P>
<P>
Clinton was the first U.S. president to visit Romania in more
than two decades.
</P>
<P>
Clinton was scheduled to meet with his Romanian counterpart
Emil Constantinescu and address a mass rally in downtown
Bucharest, before leaving for Denmark in the evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
