<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Almost Unchanged on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Share prices moved in a narrow
range on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index finished almost unchanged, falling by merely 1.2
points to close at 1967.14 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 139.26 million units, worth
347.84 million Singapore dollars (about 243.24 million U.S.
dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines by 232 to 90 while 306
other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Mullah R was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 12.2 million units. It was followed by Magnum
Corporation which had 5.09 million shares traded. The Raffles
Medical Group was next with 4.52 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 1.2 dollars to finish at 27.9 Singapore
dollars. GE Life gained 60 cents to end at 16.1 Singapore dollars
while Gentings closed 35 cents higher at 6.45 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, ERL was the biggest loser as it declined by 34
cents to end at 2 dollars. Local car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage
(C&AMP;C) fell by 30 cents to close at 13.7 Singapore dollars and
Robinson finished 25 cents lower at 7.15 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
