<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rubber Production Increases in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam produced 50,862 tons of
dried latex in the first six months of the year, achieving a
year-on-year increase of 6.5 percent, according to the Vietnam
Rubber Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Agreeable weather and 7,794 additional hectares of rubber trees
reaching maturity this year contributed to the growing output.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the corporation earned 16.2 million U.S. dollars
from exporting 13,000 tons of rubber.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam now has 270,000 hectares of rubber trees which can
produce an estimated 160,000 tons of dried latex per year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
