<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Seeks UN Endorsement of Reinstalling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nigerian foreign minister, Chief Tom Ikimi yesterday in New York
briefed the UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan on the situation in Sierra
Leone and the ECOWAS's intention there.
</P>
<P>
Ikimi is the head of the ECOWAS Committee of Four on the Sierra
Leonean crisis, which comprise foreign ministers of Nigeria, Ghana,
Guinea and Cote d'Ivoire.
</P>
<P>
He told the the U.N. secretary-general that UN's endorsement would send "the
right signal to the illegal regime in Sierra Leone".
</P>
<P>
In its recent meeting in Conakry, Guinea, the Committee of Four
decided to employ dialogue, sanctions and forces in toppling the
military government of Major Johnny Koromah established after the May
25 coup.
</P>
<P>
Ikimi has planned to meet with the UN Security Council later
Thursday. The result of the meeting is not known at the moment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
