<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Works out Guidelines for Road Repair Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has worked out a document
to stipulate how funds for road construction and rehabilitation
will be sourced and used.
</P>
<P>
The document, prepared by the Ministry of Communications and
Transport, also addresses the problem of road reconstruction and
rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
Zambia, which needs more than 65 billion Kwacha (about 50
million U.S. Dollars) yearly for effective road maintenance,
can generate only 15 billion Kwacha (about 12 million Dollars).
</P>
<P>
A large proportion of country's road networks was constructed
in the early 1960s and has now reached the last stage of its
designed life.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that only 20 percent of the paved road
networks is now in good condition, whereas 30 percent are graded
as in fair condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
