<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Higher as Gold Rebounds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Higher gold and base metal prices
overnight sparked a resurgence in the gold sector, pushing the
Australian share market to a higher close today.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark All Ordinaries Index rose 4.7 points to 2699.1,
off its earlier intraday high of 2703.7.
</P>
<P>
"It was pretty much due to the gold stocks which were stronger
on the back of gold prices overnight and the base metals were
reasonably strong as well," a Brisbane-based broker said.
</P>
<P>
The gold sector surged 4.84 percent or 60 points to 1299.4,
while in Sydney, gold bullion was trading at 320.6 U.S. dollars an
ounce, 1 dollar higher than yesterday's close.
</P>
<P>
The All Resources Index rose 14.2 points to 1444.3, led by
performers such as oil and gas interests Woodside Petroleum and
Santos.
</P>
<P>
Woodside added 40.5 cents to 11.47 Australian dollars while
Santos finished 20 cents firmer at 6 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials Index shed 5.1 points to 4313.7 while the
banking index added 17.3 points to 5066.8.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 321.99 million shares worth 762.22
Australian dollars (564 million U.S. dollars), with rises
outnumbering falls by 661 to 474.  
</P>
</TEXT>
