<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Oldest Chinese Newspaper on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's oldest Chinese
newspaper, Kwong Wah Yit Poh, today launched its own homepage on
the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Kwong Wah Yit Poh, with its headquarters in Malaysia's
northwest state of Pulau Pinang, was founded in 1910 by Dr. Sun
Yat-sen, who led the revolution in 1911 overthrowing the feudal
Qing Dynasty in China.
</P>
<P>
The Kwong Wah homepage is available to Internet users at
http://www.kwongwah.com.my. And news on the Kwong Wah homepage is
updated every day at 7:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
The daily provides foreign and local news as well as
information relating to the company and its subsidiaries, Color
Lab Private Ltd. and Kwong Wah Realty. 
