<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
rose today, but closed off earlier highs on a statement from the
Reserve Bank that monetary conditions were too loose.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended nine points higher at 2516 with a
turnover of 61 million NZ dollars (40 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
All leaders gained. Telecom shares rose 2 cents to 784 cents,
Fletcher Paper 1 cent to 347 cents and Brierley Investment 3 cents
higher to 139 cents. Carter Holt Harvey climbed 3 cents to 370
cents while Air New Zealand edged up 1 cent to 311 cents and Lion
Nathan 6 cents to 388 cents.
</P>
<P>
There were 58 rises and 42 falls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
