<HEADLINE> Second-Round Cyprus Talks Set for August in Geneva </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of the Greek and
Turkish Cypriot communities agreed to hold a second round of talks
on the Cyprus problem near Geneva between August 11 and 16,
reports reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan opened the five-day Cyprus
talks between President Glafcos Clerides, who is also head of the
Greek Cypriot community, and Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash
on Wednesday at Troutbeck, a rural resort 145 kilometers north of
New York City.
</P>
<P>
The talks were aimed to reunite the divided island as a
bi-zonal, bi-communal federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
