<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Becomes Large Trading Partner of Shijiazhuang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 11 (Xinhua) --Hong Kong has become the
biggest trading partner of Shijiazhuang, the capital of Hebei
Province.
</P>
<P>
The city has 1,100 overseas-backed enterprises, involving 816 million
U.S. dollars in overseas investment since opening to the outside
world 17 years ago. Of these, Hong Kong investors have invested
440 million U.S. dollars in 519 businesses.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong-backed businesses in the city range from industrial,
commercial, and tourist to construction of infrastructure, public
facilities, education, and public welfare projects.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongying, deputy mayor of the city, says that they hope
exchanges and economic cooperation between Shijiazhuang and Hong
Kong will increase after July 1.
</P>
<P>
Li also welcomes more companies and businessmen from Hong Kong
to invest or do business in the northern Chinese city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
