<DOCNO> XIE19970711.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Makes Headway in Enterprise Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north China
has made remarkable headway in initiating a modern enterprise
system in state-owned firms, which has already invigorated pilot
companies in the project.
</P>
<P>
So far, 162 enterprises have been transformed into
share-holding companies and 50 more firms are experimenting with
the modern enterprise system.
</P>
<P>
The system, which represents the higher degree of autonomy that
is gaining ground in the internal administration of many
enterprises, is a pivotal step taken by the central authorities
to enliven its loss-making State sector.
</P>
<P>
Pilot reforms are now in full swing across China, especially in
major industrial bases such as Shanghai and Liaoning.
</P>
<P>
Companies that have ushered in the modern enterprise system
have become core firms in enterprise groups and positive results
from the reforms are already evident.  
</P>
</TEXT>
