<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak to Provide Population Service at Every Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government is
undertaking to provide a population service at every health
facility throughout the country over the next two years, said
Federal Minister for Population Welfare Syeda Abida Hussain.
</P>
<P>
In an interview here today with the local press on the eve of
the World Population Day, she said the government was launching
this program for population welfare.
</P>
<P>
"This (Program) would be in addition to the family planning
centers in the private sector run by non-governmental
organizations (NGOs) as well as those by the government that are
already in place," said Abida.
</P>
<P>
The population service will be provided at every health
facility throughout the country, she added.
</P>
<P>
In Pakistan, the World Population Day will be observed with a
National Population Convention here to be inaugurated by Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif.  
</P>
</TEXT>
