<HEADLINE> Various Social Sectors Encouraged to Run Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Enterprises, social
organizations and individuals have become an important driving
force in educational reform in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
By now, the number of non-government-owned schools has reached
1,927, enrolling 300,000 students.
</P>
<P>
The participation by different social sectors in education was
first seen in the province in 1984, when four retired workers set
up a medical school.
</P>
<P>
By now, the province's non-government-owned schools have a total
floor space of nearly two million sq.m., 130 million yuan (about
16.2 million US dollars) worth of educational equipment and nearly
50 million books.
</P>
<P>
About 3.5 million people have graduated from these schools.
</P>
</TEXT>
