<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Africa Full of Economic Bounce, Says Australian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 11 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is full of
economic bounce which makes it an attractive trading partner, Tim
Fischer, visiting Australian Trade Minister and Deputy Prime
Minister, said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the end of the first Australia-South Africa Joint
Ministerial Commission meeting in Pretoria, Fischer said the
prospects of doing business in South Africa were bright, a local
daily The Citizen reported today.
</P>
<P>
"The message we will be taking back is that there is a great
deal of expansion potential in two-way trade, investment and
tourism between South Africa and Australia," said Fischer
who arrived in the country on Tuesday for a three-day
visit.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Thursday, Fischer and South African Trade and
Industry Minister Alec Erwin signed a wide-ranging memorandum of
understanding on cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, the two sides also agreed on an
action plan which was described as a framework for the expansion
of a multi-billion dollar trade between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The governments of Australia and South Africa would help their
companies to use the each other country as a base for trading in Asia
and Africa, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the two-way trade between South Africa
and Australia has been increasing at a growth rate of 35 percent
each year since 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
