<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China Hi-Tech Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Daqing Hi-Tech Development Zone
in north China's Heilongjiang province has had 4.05 billion yuan
in industrial output value and 937 million yuan in pre-tax profits
since it was established in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ruiming, a State Science and Technology Commission
official said that, in spite of the hardships the development zone
has faced, it is now in a leading position among the country's 52
hi-tech development zones.
</P>
<P>
By making use of preferential policies, Daqing has attracted
technicians and experts, and now has 285 enterprises, with 425
types of products. It had two billion yuan in industrial output
value in 1996, an increase of 102 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Daqing has had 28 production lines in operation since early
last year, eight of which have an output value of more than 100
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Daqing had 18 "Torch Project" programs, whose purpose
is to promote development of new and high-tech industries, and
received 37 million yuan in loans from the government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
