<HEADLINE> Pak Cabinet Expanded by 13 New Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's federal cabinet was
expanded today with nine new ministers and four new ministers of
state taking oath of office at a simple ceremony.
</P>
<P>
President Farooq Leghari administered the oath at the ceremony
held at the presidency here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and federal ministers were present
on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
The ministers who took oath are Raja Muhammad Zafarul Haq,
Shaikh Rashid Ahmed, Raja Nadir Pervez, Sardar Yaqub Khan,
Makhdoom Javed Hashemi, Syed Ghous Ali Shah, Yasin Wattoo, Majid
Malik and Abdul Sattar Laleka.
</P>
<P>
The four ministers of state are Tahmina Daultana, Siddiq Kanju,
 Halim Siddiqui and Makhdoom Ahmed Mahmood.
</P>
<P>
The federal cabinet now comprises 23 members -- 16 ministers
and five ministers of state.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mushahid Hussain Sayed and Khalid Anwar have been
appointed advisors to the prime minister.  
</P>
</TEXT>
