<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Antimony Base Revives Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Technical reform and optimized
product mix have helped Mount Xikuang in central China's Hunan
Province recover its past glory, according to Liu Xueming, head of
the Mount Xikuang Mining Bureau.
</P>
<P>
According to Liu, large-scale technological transformation
conducted in three subsidiary refineries of the bureau has raised
the antimony and antimony-related production capacity to the
present 31,000 tons annually from 14,000 tons in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The annual output increase has been steady at 3,000 tons in
past few years, enabling Mount Xikuang to regain its world
antimony production record.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that Mount Xikuang plans to increase the annual
production of chlor-alkali by 10,000 tons by the end of this
year. Moreover, he added, a 10,000-ton expansion program for zinc
ore and two other sideline production projects have been listed in
next year's schedule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
