<HEADLINE> Sino-German Gypsum Plant To Be Built in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 11 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese company has signed a
40-year agreement with a German partner to open a gypsum factory
in Zaozhuang city in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The contract was signed Thursday at Shandong's Qingdao Foreign
Trade Fair by Shandong's Lunan Gypsum Group and the German Knauf
Group. an investment of 31.8 million US dollars will be used to
set up the Lunan-Knauf Gypsum Plate Co. Ltd., with 69 percent of
that coming from the German company.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture is designed to produce 20 million sq m of
various sizes and types of gypsum plate annually. Half of the
products will be exported.  
</P>
</TEXT>
