<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebels Send Squad to Kill Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 11 (Xinhua) -- A fully armed suicide squad sent
by Sri Lanka's rebel Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) has
arrived in a town in the northeast of the country on a mission to
kill four senior security personnel there, security sources said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The previous attempt by the LTTE rebels to kill government
security personnel in Trincomalee town, some 250 km from Colombo,
was made in December last year, when a lone suicide bomber jumped
into the vehicle of a police officer.
</P>
<P>
The police officer was not in the vehicle, but his driver was
killed.
</P>
<P>
Last week the rebels assassinated Tamil Parliamentarian
Arunachalam Thangathurai in Trincomalee, where he was attending a
school function. Five others also died in the incident.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been waging a 14-year-old guerrilla war for a
separate state in the north and east of the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
