<HEADLINE> Environmentally-Friendly Buses Running in Southwest China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- A number of
environmentally-friendly buses using compressed natural gas as
fuel are operating on the streets of Chengdu, the capital of
southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the traditional buses that use gasoline or diesel
fuel, these emit far fewer harmful gasses into the air, and have
gotten a good reception by the public since being put to use.
</P>
<P>
Officials say that this kind of bus will account for about half
the city's buses by the end of the century.  
</P>
