<HEADLINE> Italy Urges Institutional Reform of EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini said here today that the institutional reform of the European
Union (EU) must be pushed forward.
</P>
<P>
The future of Europe should focus on politics, said Dini. He
spoke after the reading of the report by the Committee on Foreign
Relations of the Italian Senate on the EU Amsterdam Summit, in
June.
</P>
<P>
"While the 'political Europe,' is talked about, the suspended
institutional reform should be referred to," said Dini, "The EU
will not enlarge when institutional reform is not carried out."
</P>
<P>
As for the reform, the foreign minister said Italy hoped to let
more members join the voting.
</P>
<P>
The Amsterdam Summit concluded two years of negotiations on EU
internal reform that were intended to ensure the 15-nation bloc
could still function when it expanded to 20 or more. 
</P>
</TEXT>
