<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Population Reaches 45.5 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's population is estimated
to have reached 45.5 million, rising by about 800,000 annually in
recent years, the state-run newspaper the New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
If the present annual growth rate of 1.9 percent is maintained,
Myanmar's population is expected to reach 68.5 million in the year
2020, the paper quoted Minister for Immigration and Population
Maung Hla as predicting.
</P>
<P>
The population of Myanmar stood at 16 million in 1941, and
35.5 million in the 1983 population census, which more than
doubled in 42 years, the paper said in an article marking the
World Population day.
</P>
<P>
It added that urban dwellers in Myanmar have been on the rise,
with the percentage of urban people in the whole population rose
from 23.6 percent in 1973 to 24 percent in 1983.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official statistics, the population of
Yangon, capital of Myanmar, has exceeded 5 million.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said Myanmar had drafted a population policy to
ensure a rational ratio between the country's population and area
and had laid out plans to guarantee health and fitness for all
families.
</P>
<P>
For example, it said, a children's development project
initiated in 1992 has been successfully carried out in the whole
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
