<HEADLINE> Wright Fined and Warned by FA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Arsenal striker Ian Wright was
handed one of English soccer's largest fines for misconduct on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Football Association (FA) fined Wright 15,000 pounds
(25,200 U.S. dollars) for physical and verbal abuse of officials
and opponents during two matches last April.
</P>
<P>
Wright was also warned that he would be thrown out of the games
for a long time if he got in trouble again.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old England international, who is presently
undergoing counselling to control his temper, was fined for
remarks he made to the referee after a game against Blackburn and
obscene gestures he made to the crowd at Coventry.
</P>
<P>
FA spokesman David Davies said an F.A. commission had made it
clear to Wright during a hearing on Thursday that he would face a
very long ban if his poor behaviour continued. 
</P>
