<HEADLINE> Belarus Economy Takes Favorable Turn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The economy in Belarus took a
favorable turn during the first half this year, the Interfax news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Material released by the country's Prime Minister, Sergei Ling,
says the gross domestic product (GDP) increased by 11 percent
during the half year compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Outputs of industry, agriculture and consumer goods increased
by 13.9 percent, 4.2 percent and 24.3 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The investment in fixed assets increased by 15 percent and
turnover from the retail trade by 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
Ling said people's living standards had risen, to some extent
due to the improving economy. During the six months people's real
incomes increased by 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister said some problems remained in economic
sectors which had to be solved. They included the higher inflation
rate, which reached 6 percent. 
</P>
