<HEADLINE> Hunan Boosts Export-Oriented Processing Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan province
recorded more than one billion US dollars-worth of foreign trade
during the first five months of this year, 276 million US
dollars-worth of which was connected with the processing trade, a
20 percent rise from the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Processing export accounted for 28 percent of the total foreign
trade volume. This was a result of local efforts to encourage
export-oriented processing businesses by issuing a series of
preferential policies, involving taxation, loans, transportation
and energy supply.
</P>
<P>
Hunan places particular stress on the processing businesses in
the local open and developed cities and regions with convenient
transport links. The export-oriented processing areas include
south Hunan bordering Guangdong province, north Hunan areas
linking Chenglingji Port and the triangle area linking Changsha,
Zhuzhou and Xiangtang cities. 
</P>
