<HEADLINE> Technological Exchanges Boom in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The mushrooming
technology-trading organizations in central China's Henan province
have given a great impetus to a local drive for the application of
technological achievements.
</P>
<P>
The province had more than 7,000 undertakings involved in this
sector in 1996, with the number of employees reaching
110,000. Over the past ten years the "go-betweens" have helped
the province deal with as many as 130,000 technological contracts,
involving nearly seven billion yuan in business value.
</P>
<P>
Frequent trade fairs, auctions and announcements of new
technologies in Henan have provided a basis for the province to
exchange information, skills and techniques. The past ten-year
period also witnessed the local state enterprises introduce more
than 1.6 billion yuan-worth of technological advances while
transfering nearly 1.9 billion yuan-worth of its achievements. The
business volume accounted for two-fifths of the local total for
technological contracts during the same period.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there are also more than 3,000 organizations in
the sector in the rural areas, handling 150 million yuan in
turnover a year. They are expected to give a boost to the local
rural economic development by taking practical skills and
techniques to the countryside.  
</P>
</TEXT>
