<HEADLINE> South China City's Exports Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- South China's Liuzhou City in
Guangxi Province earned a record 119.2 million US dollars
worth of foreign exchange from exports in the first half of the
year, an increase of over 10 percent compared with the same period
of last year.
</P>
<P>
The city's trade has expanded to more than 40 countries, and it
now has nearly 130 types of commodities.
</P>
<P>
The city earned 25.48 million dollars from processing with
imported materials in the first half of the year, which doubles the
goal for the year.
</P>
<P>
Its 30-plus overseas-funded firms earned nearly 17.7 million
dollars from exports, nearly twice as much as that of the same
period of 1996. The city's mechanical and electrical equipment
sells quite well on the world market.  
