<HEADLINE> IDB Launches 200 Mln Dlr Yankee Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank today announced the launching of a 200 million U.S. dollar
bond issue under the U.S. Medium-Term Note Program.
</P>
<P>
The bond issue has a coupon payable semiannually of 6.29
percent and a maturity date of July 16, 2027.
</P>
<P>
Investors have a one-time option to put the bonds to the IDB at
100 percent of the principal amount on July 16, 2007.
</P>
<P>
Merrill Lynch is the lead manager of the issue, which was
priced at 100 percent.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the issue will be incorporated into the IDB's
ordinary capital and will be used to finance economic and social
development in Latin America and the Caribbean. 
