<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Turn Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street rose
modestly today amid some encouraging profit reports and optimism
that Friday's report on wholesale prices will be encouraging.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 44.33 points to 7,886.76.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 551.27 million
shares as against 589.08 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 6.24 to 913.78, and
the NYSE composite index rose 3.24 to 476.27.
</P>
<P>
Setting new highs was the Nasdaq composite index, up 4.30 to
1,490.93.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange composite index, which is dominated
by smaller companies, rose 0.68 to 631.70. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
